%S A392651 53235,91035,101115,103005,106785,109395,113715,120015,122265,123795,
%T A392651 129465,131355,140805,142695,148005,148365,154035,157815,159885,
%U A392651 163485,166005,166635,168525,169155,171045,171675,173565,177975,180495,182385,185535,186165,186615
%N A392651 Odd solid numbers that are not odd primitive abundant numbers. A number k is solid if a subset of its sum-irreducible nontrivial divisors sums to k. Sum-irreducible divisors are defined in A392650.
%C A392651 [In A195101 the author also refers to his numbers as 'solid numbers'. These are unrelated to the numbers presented here.]
%e A392651 n = 53235 is a term of this sequence, because 3 + 7 + 315 + 845 + 1183 + 1365 + 1521 + 2535 + 3549 + 5915 + 7605 + 10647 + 17745 = 53235. All summands are divisors of n and sum-irreducible.
%o A392651 (SageMath)
%o A392651 # The function 'is_sum_irreducible' is defined in A392650.
%o A392651 # The function 'subset_sum_exists' is defined in A392652.
%o A392651 def is_A392651(n) -> bool:
%o A392651     if n < 53235 or n % 2 == 0: return False
%o A392651     divs = divisors(n)[1:-1]
%o A392651     irr_divs = [d for d in divs if is_sum_irreducible(d)]
%o A392651     return subset_sum_exists(irr_divs, n)
%o A392651 A = [n for n in range(1, 186616) if is_A392651(n)]; print(A)
%Y A392651 Cf. A006038, A392649, A392650, A392652.
%K A392651 nonn,new
%O A392651 1,1
